<font color="#FF0000">EXTREMELY GRATEFUL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Apr  8 20:51:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I'm speechless.  There are so many feelings racing through my body right now that I am absolutely speechless. But, my pounding heart, my turning stomach and my moistened eyes talk for me.  I'm 21 years old and until this past week have known practically nothing about the Vietnam War.  I suppose I can thank the school systems for that.  They preach about the Revolutionary War, Civil War, World Wars I and II, but why not the Vietnam War?  It is so important that the younger generations are aware of the pure hell our vets went through, not only during the war, but after the war as well.  I am so sorry and embarrassed that this country, to this day, cannot be more understanding of what our vets have endured and are still enduring.  Please, never stop voicing your feelings and experiences.... it is the only way others, like myself, will ever learn of what happened.  Thank you for everything all of you have done.
<p><code>-- bergerel@pilot.msu.edu  (Beth) </code><p>


